<TITLE> 3 ICS member arrested in Pirijpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pirojpur, July 3 (bdnews24.com)Police on Friday arrested three members of Islami Chhatri Sangstha, the Jamaat-e-Islami's female student front, at a madrasa in Pirojpur, suspecting them to involved in criminal activities. Books written by party founder Syed Abul Al Moududi and Delwar Hossain Sayeedi, reports on organisation members and a few diaries were recovered from Tania Akhter, 26, a primary school teacher and resident of Parerhat Road in Pirojpur town, Syeda Fouzia Akhter, 18, of Machhimpur, and Jesmin Nahar, 20, of Zianagar thana. The court sent them to jail. Sub-inspector of Zianagar Police Station Amar Singh told bdnews24.com on information from the local people the police went to the madrasa and found the women in the common room. Chandraban Bibi, 35, wife of Motaleb Sikder, was in their custody. They said they had come to attend the members' conference. Principal of the madrasa Ziaul Huq was not available for comments. Officer-in-charge of Zianagar police Abdur Razzaq told bdnews24.com quoting local people that Huq was involved with the Jamaat-e-Islami. bdnew
